<plot>Bill Stern recaps the winners of various college sports for the 1941-42 NCAA championships, ranging from Lacrosse, Rowing, Basketball, Football, and Track &amp; Field champions. Most of these represented the last true level-field champions until after World War II, as the majority of college athletes of those 1942-46 years were in the armed services. Teams shown include the University of Washington team that won the Poughkeepsie Regatta, the Army-Navy lacrosse teams, the Long Island University basketball team, and the football game between George Tech's 'Ramblin' Wrecks' and Notre Dame's 'Fighting Irish.'</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?111238</url></doc>
